The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 December is 304,335 (35,076.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 December, there were 579 new confirmed cases (66.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 December, there were 473 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 22% (106 extra cases).
